    "course_title": "ADVANCED REGRESSION METHODS FOR POPULATION HEALTH",
    "description": "Extension of regression analysis to observational data with unequal variance, unequal sampling and propensity weights, clusters and longitudinal measurements, using different variance structures, mixed linear models, generalized linear models and GEE.  Matrix notation will be introduced and underlying mathematical and statistical principles will be explained.  Examples use data sets from ongoing population health research.",
